Both nickel and chromium have good corrosion resistance at high temperatures. In this article, we will introduce the different types of Inconel alloys one by one.</p><time class="media-time">2022.11.08</time><div class="media-div">Learn More</div></a></div><div class="point"></div><div class="media-blog"><a href="/AEETHER/media/media-62/media.html"><img loading="lazy" src="/AEETHER/media/media-62/mediapic1.jpg" alt="title image for related articles"><h4><span>Everything You need to Know about ASTM B670</span></h4><p class="media-p">ASTM B670 is mainly applicable to Inconel 718 (UNS N07718) sheet, plate, coil and strip. In this article, we will summarize the important points and details of ASTM B670. This helps you have more control over quality when purchasing materials.</p><time class="media-time">2022.10.24</time><div class="media-div">Learn More</div></a></div><div class="point"></div><div class="media-blog"><a href="/AEETHER/media/media-53/media.html"><img loading="lazy" src="/AEETHER/media/media-53/mediapic1.jpg" alt="title image for related articles"><h4><span>The Role of Niobium in Superalloys</span></h4><p class="media-p">Niobium plays a role in both solid solution strengthening and precipitation strengthening in superalloys. In this article, we will describe them clearly.</p><time class="media-time">2022.05.23</time><div class="media-div">Learn More</div></a></div><div class="point"></div><div class="media-blog"><a href="/AEETHER/media/media-38/media.html"><img loading="lazy" src="/AEETHER/media/media-38/mediapic1.jpg" alt="title image for related articles"><h4><span>The Role of Aluminum in Superalloys</span></h4><p class="media-p">Aluminum plays a very important role in some superalloys. This article will fully let you understand why aluminum is added to some alloys.</p><time class="media-time">2021.12.13</time><div class="media-div">Learn More</div></a></div><div class="point"></div><div class="media-blog"><a href="/AEETHER/media/media-20/media.html"><img loading="lazy" src="/AEETHER/media/media-20/mediapic1.jpg" alt="title image for related articles"><h4><span>The Role of Titanium in Superalloys</span></h4><p class="media-p">Titanium is a very stable metal. This article will discuss the role of titanium in superalloys and the effect of the ratio of titanium to aluminum on precipitation strengthening.</p><time class="media-time">2021.12.13</time><div class="media-div">Learn More</div></a></div><div class="point"></div><div class="media-blog"><a href="/AEETHER/media/media-36/media.html"><img loading="lazy" src="/AEETHER/media/media-36/mediapic1.jpg" alt="title image for related articles"><h4><span>The Role of Iron in Superalloys</span></h4><p class="media-p">Iron is the most common element in superalloys. In this article, we will discuss the respective roles of iron in the three types of superalloys.</p><time class="media-time">2021.12.11</time><div class="media-div">Learn More</div></a></div><div class="point"></div><div class="media-blog"><a href="/AEETHER/media/media-33/media.html"><img loading="lazy" src="/AEETHER/media/media-33/mediapic1.jpg" alt="title image for related articles"><h4><span>Inconel Alloy 625 VS Inconel Alloy 718</span></h4><p class="media-p">The main difference between them is that the performance of Inconel 625 is more towards corrosion resistance, while the performance of Inconel 718 is more towards high strength. This article will compare alloy 625 and alloy 718 from all aspects.</p><time class="media-time">2021.11.30</time><div class="media-div">Learn More</div></a></div><div class="point"></div><div class="media-blog"><a href="/AEETHER/media/media-32/media.html"><img loading="lazy" src="/AEETHER/media/media-32/mediapic1.jpg" alt="title image for related articles"><h4><span>Clearly Understand Superalloys through 3 Classification ...</span></h4><p class="media-p">Up to hundreds of alloy grades may make you feel confused. In this article, we will classify superalloys from three aspects. From then on, you will have a clearer understanding of superalloys.</p><time class="media-time">2021.11.11</time><div class="media-div">Learn More</div></a></div><div class="point"></div><div class="media-blog"><a href="/AEETHER/media/media-30/media.html"><img loading="lazy" src="/AEETHER/media/media-30/mediapic1.jpg" alt="title image for related articles"><h4><span>What is Precipitation Strengthening & Aging Treatment ...</span></h4><p class="media-p">In the last article, we introduced the principle of solid solution strengthening and common solid solution strengthening alloys. In this article, we will continue to introduce precipitation strengthening and precipitation strengthening alloys.</p><time class="media-time">2021.10.25</time><div class="media-div">Learn More</div></a></div><div class="point"></div><div class="media-blog"><a href="/AEETHER/media/media-18/media.html"><img loading="lazy" src="/AEETHER/media/media-18/mediapic1.jpg" alt="title image for related articles"><h4><span>The Influence of Manganese on Superalloys</span></h4><p class="media-p">In this article, we will discuss in detail the role and influence of manganese in superalloys from 5 aspects.</p><time class="media-time">2021.08.29</time><div class="media-div">Learn More</div></a></div><div class="point"></div><div class="media-blog"><a href="/AEETHER/media/media-21/media.html"><img loading="lazy" src="/AEETHER/media/media-21/mediapic1.jpg" alt="title image for related articles"><h4><span>What is the Difference Between Monel, Inconel, ...?</span></h4><p class="media-p">Monel 400, Monel K-500, Inconel 600, Inconel 625, Inconel 718, ... and Hastelloy C-276 are the most common nickel alloy grades.  In this article, we will explore together the role and influence of different chemical elements in these grades.</p><time class="media-time">2021.01.05</time><div class="media-div">Learn More</div></a></div><div class="point"></div><div class="media-blog"><a href="/AEETHER/media/media-5/media.html"><img loading="lazy" src="/AEETHER/media/media-5/mediapic1.jpg" alt="title image for related articles"><h4><span>The Outlook of Nickel Alloy Application in Aviation ...</span></h4><p class="media-p">Thanks to the advancement of new technology, an increasing amount of newly developed nickel alloys materials now become accessible, bringing benefits to aviation industry. Nickel-based super alloy is developed to increase the operation temperature ...</p><time class="media-time">2018.08.22</time><div class="media-div">Learn More</div></a></div>                </div>
